<paragraph blockId="13.[192,1440,194,698]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[240,371,481,505]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Abdomen</emphasis>
. Urosternites with grayish pubescence (more brownish depending of angle of incision of light), mixed by long, sparse setae; urosternites I–IV finely, sparsely punctate; urosternite V moderately coarsely punctate on distal half. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[592,656,546,570]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Legs</emphasis>
. Pubescence grayish, distinctly brown-yellowish around apex of tibiae (mainly meso- and metatibiae).
</paragraph>
