</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="12" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[192,1440,1025,1274]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,316,1026,1050]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Galileo &amp; Martins &amp; Tirant &amp; Santos-Silva" authorityYear="2014" box="[330,706,1026,1050]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Esthlogena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bella" subGenus="Pseudotaxia">
<emphasis box="[330,467,1026,1050]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Esthlogena</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[482,632,1026,1050]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Pseudotaxia</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[646,706,1026,1050]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">bella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Thomson, 1868" authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1868" box="[862,1261,1025,1050]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Esthlogena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="proletaria" subGenus="Pseudotaxia">
<emphasis box="[862,889,1026,1049]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">E.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[904,929,1026,1049]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">P.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[944,1066,1026,1050]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">proletaria</emphasis>
Thomson, 1868
</taxonomicName>
, mainly by the discal tubercles on pronotum less distinctly elevated (well-elevated in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1868" box="[1075,1286,1058,1082]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Esthlogena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="proletaria" subGenus="Pseudotaxia">
<emphasis box="[1075,1102,1058,1081]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">E.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1121,1146,1058,1081]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">P.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1164,1286,1058,1082]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">proletaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and by the pronotal pubescence almost totally obliterating the integument (not so in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1868" box="[1101,1308,1090,1114]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Esthlogena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="proletaria" subGenus="Pseudotaxia">
<emphasis box="[1101,1128,1090,1113]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">E.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1144,1170,1090,1113]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">P.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1186,1308,1090,1114]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">proletaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). It differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Breuning, 1940" authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1940" box="[259,666,1122,1146]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Esthlogena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obliquata" subGenus="Pseudotaxia">
<emphasis box="[259,286,1122,1145]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">E.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[304,330,1122,1145]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">P.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[348,465,1122,1146]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">obliquata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Breuning, S." box="[475,666,1122,1146]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" pagination="115 - 214" refId="ref8306" refString="Breuning, S. 1940. Novae species Cerambycidarum. IX. Folia Zoologica et Hydrobiologica 10 (1): 115 - 214." type="journal article" year="1940">Breuning, 1940</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by the scutellum mostly with dark pubescence (whitish in 
